ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">writing=
 about</a> a Sanford C. Bernstein &amp; Co. research note arguing that =E2=
=80=9CPassive Investing is Worse Than Marxism=E2=80=9D because passive inve=
stors do not try to allocate capital to its best uses, but just buy whateve=
r is in the index.=C2=A0<em>If that were true </em>=E2=80=94=C2=A0if financ=
ial markets have abdicated their responsibility to allocate resources using=
